The paper deals with algorithms for solving algebraic systems, which is a topic in computational algebraic geometry. Therefore, cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are both likely categories. The paper also involves the computation of linear forms, which is a topic in linear algebra, and the use of bit complexity analysis, which is a topic in numerical analysis. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) are also possible categories.
